{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6179f7f7-8161-4069-8cd0-08768a890a66","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n## 1. Tests Appear as New (No History)\n\nMSTest v4 changed the **default test ID algorithm**. The fully-qualified test name used for reporting now differs from v3, so Azure DevOps sees them as entirely new tests.\n\n**Fix:** Add this to your `.csproj` to restore the old IDs:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestIdGenerationStrategy>Legacy</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n## 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level context** — it no longer carries a specific test name. Accessing `TestContext.TestName` throws `InvalidOperationException`.\n\n**Fix:** Remove or guard that access. If you need the name, move the logic into `[TestInitialize]` or use the instance `TestContext` property inside individual tests.\n\n## Other Key v4 Breaking Changes to Watch For\n\n| Area | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| **Parallelism** | Tests run in parallel by default. Add `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable if you have shared state. |\n| **Timeout behavior** | `[Timeout]` now uses `CancellationToken` cooperative cancellation instead of `Thread.Abort`. Long-running code must observe the token. |\n| **Assert.ThrowsException** | Now also catches derived exception types (matches `Assert.ThrowsExactly` for exact). |\n| **DataRow display** | `[DataRow]` tests use updated display-name formatting, which may also affect pipeline history. |\n| **Removed APIs** | Several deprecated members (e.g., some `TestContext` properties like `DataConnection`) are gone. |\n\nFor your specific file, the minimal fix on line 13:\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static void ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // TestContext.TestName is unavailable in class-level context in v4\n    // Move per-test logic to [TestInitialize] if needed\n}\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these fixes to your project files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f174749-a4c3-4aa0-94ee-0c61d446d0e1","outputTokens":542,"requestId":"9831:132E33:1365BE9:1861BEB:69FFF63F"},"id":"691a7059-38d6-4394-a623-f59dbcad610b","timestamp":"2026-05-10T03:06:53.107Z","parentId":"a114a12b-d638-4e69-9ba7-55b2b3382070"}
